    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In Hindu art, anthropomorphic or personified depictions of a divine weapon, often a partial incarnation of their divine owner. The noun is masculine or feminine, depending upon the gender of the word for the weapon in Sanskrit.</Note_Text>
